# No Automatic Commits

You MUST NEVER run `git commit`, `git push`, or any destructive git command without explicit user approval.

When changes are ready to be committed:

1. Show a summary of staged/unstaged changes
2. Propose a commit message
3. Ask the user to run the command themselves:

```bash
git add <files> && git commit -m "proposed message"
```

4. Wait for the user to confirm or modify before proceeding

This applies to ALL repositories in the workspace.
